y points are recent exposure (holiday activities), manipulation of the ear with possible trauma, and the symptoms pointing to an external ear infection.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033372,0.069981,0.083537,0.090277,0.092963,0.094823,0.094717,0.092739,0.0927,0.093304,0.084444,0.077142],"unified_progress":[0.057801,0.085179,0.087772,0.093148,0.093147,0.092897,0.090989,0.09031,0.086435,0.085189,0.074398,0.062733]},{"section":24,"text":"Otitis externa is the most common diagnosis here.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029129,0.063332,0.079485,0.086731,0.088356,0.086983,0.089079,0.087525,0.088505,0.093355,0.090685,0.11683],"unified_progress":[0.030449,0.054066,0.068092,0.078638,0.081667,0.088129,0.089216,0.091277,0.094487,0.098584,0.10651,0.11888]},{"section":25,"text":"But is there a fungal component?","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027531,0.064263,0.083167,0.09077,0.093779,0.092877,0.094859,0.095446,0.095056,0.095883,0.087761,0.078609],"unified_progress":[0.034107,0.0629,0.076998,0.088053,0.091756,0.093052,0.096785,0.098567,0.098117,0.1002,0.088483,0.070985]},{"section":26,"text":"Swimmer's ear is typically bacterial (like Pseudomonas), but if the infection isn't responding to standard treatment, fungal might be considered.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027995,0.06257,0.077216,0.087314,0.094824,0.09873,0.1016,0.10014,0.096137,0.094709,0.085196,0.07357],"unified_progress":[0.038125,0.064861,0.077157,0.084672,0.091767,0.097686,0.098234,0.099991,0.097685,0.096414,0.084923,0.068485]},{"section":27,"text":"However, the case doesn't mention prior treatment failure.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025172,0.058092,0.073525,0.082847,0.091116,0.097391,0.10172,0.10357,0.10266,0.098675,0.092008,0.07322],"unified_progress":[0.045254,0.07124,0.078786,0.086703,0.091776,0.092303,0.096225,0.098342,0.095708,0.10091,0.083217,0.059537]},{"section":28,"text":"The discharge is watery, which might lean more toward bacterial.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030421,0.06356,0.076028,0.083812,0.090063,0.093651,0.097974,0.098412,0.098618,0.096076,0.090996,0.080389],"unified_progress":[0.048795,0.065949,0.077624,0.085945,0.091696,0.093895,0.096427,0.096355,0.095203,0.093711,0.084673,0.069726]},{"section":29,"text":"Fungal might have more debris or a musty odor.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027692,0.062009,0.074648,0.084247,0.092042,0.097185,0.10307,0.10299,0.10094,0.096435,0.088653,0.070094],"unified_progress":[0.04842,0.064022,0.077589,0.085486,0.093782,0.097384,0.098827,0.10057,0.09795,0.096687,0.081193,0.058086]},{"section":30,"text":"But without more info, bacterial otitis externa is more likely.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022325,0.052504,0.06751,0.076604,0.083548,0.088622,0.095683,0.098714,0.10091,0.10101,0.10082,0.11175],"unified_progress":[0.027599,0.048983,0.061105,0.0713,0.07841,0.084698,0.089503,0.096133,0.1001,0.10681,0.1137,0.12166]},{"section":31,"text":"The patient's actions (using earbuds, nails) increase the risk.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030181,0.061714,0.071408,0.079298,0.087797,0.09628,0.098115,0.099964,0.099993,0.099127,0.094236,0.081887],"unified_progress":[0.074753,0.085654,0.078911,0.077949,0.081316,0.0857,0.086758,0.090917,0.090558,0.090187,0.085479,0.071817]},{"section":32,"text":"So, putting it all together, the most likely diagnosis is acute otitis externa, probably bacterial in origin, triggered by the activities she engaged in during her holiday.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028009,0.051933,0.059685,0.06686,0.074065,0.080633,0.086717,0.09063,0.096227,0.10025,0.10949,0.1555],"unified_progress":[0.036198,0.0447,0.052419,0.060135,0.064879,0.074072,0.079227,0.087053,